File: Around 2,700 staff will be retrenched at SAA and will be able to access the voluntary severance packages . JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Public Enterprises has welcomed Treasury's commitment to help source funding for SAA’s business rescue plan. The rescue plan requires about R10-billion for different aspects of the restructuring process. READ: Unions relieved SAA business rescue process is over This includes the emergence of a competitive national airline and severance packages for over 2,000 employees at the national carrier. SAA's business rescue plan was approved by creditors this week.